{"name":"Taited Psyker","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Though all psykers draw their power from the Warp, the Scholastica Psykana teaches that the Warp is something to fear. Some psykers ignore these warnings, whether wyrds who escaped the Black Ships, scholars of malefic lore, or even sanctioned psykers fallen from grace. Such tainted psykers embrace the true potential the Warp ofers, and even heed its denizens&rsquo; whispered promises of greater power.</p>\n<p>When making a Focus Power test, the character may gain a number of Corruption points up to his psy rating. For each point he gains in this way, he gains a +10 bonus to the Focus Power test but adds +5 to rolls on Table 6&ndash;2: Psychic Phenomena (see page 196 of the DARK HERESY Core Rulebook).</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Psy rating, Rank 2 (Trained) in Psyniscience skill, 10 Corruption points","aptitudes":"Knowledge, Psyker","benefit":"gain boni on focus power for corruption","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"2Lls0FOwS2LDBdd2"}
{"name":"Bulwark of Faith","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s faith is both a shield and a weapon. So filled with righteous fervour is he that Daemons recoil from the blinding light of his faith, their unholy forms sundered.</p>\n<p>Effect: When the character passes a Fear test caused by a Daemon, the Daemon suffers 1 Energy damage ignoring armour and Toughness bonus for each degree of success on the Fear test.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Willpower 45, Iron Faith","aptitudes":"Defence, Willpower","benefit":"passed fear test causes Deamons damage","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"34Nm8MW6haIKhMaf"}
{"name":"Purity of Hatred*","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Specialisations: Any group for which the character possesses</p>\n<p>the Hatred talent</p>\n<p>The Acolyte has honed his hatred to a razor&rsquo;s edge, pure and unsullied by mercy or doubt. When facing the object of his hatred, whether it be the witch, mutant, heretic, or traitor, the Acolyte is an instrument of the Emperor&rsquo;s Will, despatching His judgement upon the enemies of humanity as if guided by His very hand. When selecting this talent, the character chooses one specific group for which he possesses the Hatred talent. Against opponents of this group, the Acolyte&rsquo;s attacks gain the Vengeful (9) quality. If the Acolyte&rsquo;s weapon or attacks already possess this quality, decrease the value by one (to a minimum of 1).</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Hatred (Any)","aptitudes":"Ofence, Willpower","benefit":"gain Vengeful against an enemy of hatred","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"3v1ejDnaoY9jNTfu"}
{"name":"Devastating Assau","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte launches a furious attack on his foe, the rage of the Emperor powering his assault. Once per turn, after resolving an All Out Attack action that successfully hits, the character may make a second All Out Attack action against the same target as a Free Action, with the same bonuses and penalties as the first.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Weapon Skill 35","aptitudes":"Weapon Skill, Offence","benefit":"A successful All Out Attack grants a second attack.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"6s5wT35oAqH8nbdD"}
{"name":"Inspiring Aura","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s strength of will inspires those under his command and his comrades in equal measure. Looking to his faithful example, his allies can overcome their own fear in order to do the Emperor&rsquo;s work.</p>\n<p>Effect: The character can affect allies of any kind&mdash;not only subordinates&mdash;with the Terrify special use for the Command skill (see page 101 of the Dark Heresy Core Rulebook). This need not represent threats and intimidation, but might represent inspiring words, encouragement, or sheer steadfastness in the face of terrifying foes.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Halo of Command","aptitudes":"Leadership, Willpower","benefit":"effect all allies with the command skill","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"7L3W5BjCbKgEvOl1"}
{"name":"Hardened Soul","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte knows that he must sacrifice his own salvation in order to safeguard humanity, but that he must resist the corruption for as long as possible. Through practiced meditation, self-flagellation, prayer and fasting, force of will, or even sorcerous rites, the character staves off the effects of his growing corruption, delaying the inevitable.</p>\n<p>Effect: Whenever the character would gain Corruption points, he may reduce the amount gained by half (rounded up) and gain Insanity points equal to the amount reduced.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Willpower 35, 10 Corruption points","aptitudes":"Defence, Willpower","benefit":"gain insanity instead of corruption","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"7hcmjJNxxp3jgeII"}
{"name":"Independent Targetin","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte has developed his situational awareness to a point where he can fire in two directions within a split second. When firing two weapons as part of a single action (using the Two-Weapon Fighting talent, for example), the character does not need his targets to be within 10 metres of each other.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Ballistic Skill 40","aptitudes":"Ballistic Skill, Finesse","benefit":"Fire at multiple targets more than 10 metres apart","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"8Bc65XgmzE1tUwZn"}
{"name":"Warp Conduit","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The sheer power of the Acolyte&rsquo;s mind allows him to channel vast amounts of Warp energy when he chooses. When Pushing (see page 194), before rolling his Focus Power test the character may spend one Fate Point to add an additional 1d5 to the effective psy rating of the power. Channelling such vast amounts of power is dangerous, however, and so he adds +30 to rolls on Table 6&ndash;2: Psychic Phenomena when he makes as a result of this talent.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Spend Fate point to add 1d5 to psy rating.","aptitudes":"Psy rating, Strong Minded, Willpower 50","benefit":"Willpower, Psyker","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"C8PBq00q759Kd3YU"}
{"name":"Xenosavant","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>In his study and prosecution of the xenos threat, the Acolyte has become well-versed in the ways and forms of the myriad alien races that menace humanity. The character can attempt any Forbidden Lore (Xenos) test in which he is not trained as an untrained skill test as if it were not a Specialist skill.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Rank 3 in Forbidden Lore (Xenos–Any)","aptitudes":"Intelligence, Knowledge","benefit":"roll any Forbidden Lore (Xenos) test as an untrained skill test","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"GHKmjfe8ObK3LH4H"}
{"name":"Prosanguine","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Through the Acolyte&rsquo;s iron will, he is able to speed the function of his Autosanguinator. He must spend 10 minutes in meditation and make a Tech-Use test. If he succeeds, he removes 1d5 points of damage. If he rolls a 96 or higher, he loses the ability to use his Autosanguinator for one week.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Autosanguine Implants, Mechanicus Implants","aptitudes":"Toughness, Tech","benefit":"Test to heal 1d5 damage.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"GQtuUL6g4U5Pt9M0"}
{"name":"Hatred*","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p><strong>Specialisations:</strong> Chaos Space Marines, Daemons, Mutants, Psykers, Xenos (specific), others including groups from the sidebar The Powers of Askellon on page 94.</p>\n<p>A group, organisation, or race has wronged the character in the past, fuelling this animosity. When fighting opponents of that group in close combat, the Acolyte gains a +10 bonus to all Weapon Skill tests made against them. He also finds it difficult to back down from a fight with his hated foe, and must make a Challenging (+0) Willpower test to retreat or surrender when fighting them, unless suicidally outnumbered or outclassed.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"None","aptitudes":"Weapon Skill, Social","benefit":"Gain +10 bonus to attack hated creatures.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"GtRQ5EGiA6xXFQH1"}
{"name":"Daemonologist","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte is practiced in the dark arts, and knowledgeable in the strengths and vulnerabilities of Warp creatures. He is especially skilled at banishing Daemons&mdash;or harnessing them&mdash;through the use of his psychic abilities.</p>\n<p>Effect: When the character takes the Focus Power action and the target of the psychic power is a Daemon, he gains a +10 bonus to the Focus Power test. At the GM&rsquo;s discretion, this bonus may apply to other tests, such as rituals to summon or bind a Daemon.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Psy rating 3, Willpower 45, Forbidden Lore (Daemonology)","aptitudes":"Psyker, Willpower","benefit":"fokus boni against Daemons","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"HLCbCSnrjJNb40hM"}
{"name":"Mechadendrite Use*","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p><strong>Specialisations:</strong> Weapon, Utility</p>\n<p>The Acolyte is trained in the use of a particular kind of mechadendrite (see page 183) in much the same way as Weapon Training allows the use of weapons. Though there are many different types of mechadendrites, this talent divides them into two broad categories:</p>\n<p>&bull; Weapon: Mechadendrites of this type end in either ranged or close combat weapons, and have the supplemental power supplies and mechanical support necessary for combat.</p>\n<p>&bull; Utility: Including such varied types as Manipulator, Medicae, Utility, Optical, and countless others, these generally require less hardy mountings, but all function in a similar manner.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Mechanicus Implants","aptitudes":"Intelligence, Tech","benefit":"Gain ability to use certain Mechadendrites","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Ixycz28eLetBLejW"}
{"name":"Lexographer","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>From years poring over dusty tomes and examining ancient ruins on forgotten worlds&mdash;and perhaps even speaking face-toface with inhuman beings&mdash;the Acolyte has become an expert in deciphering lost human languages as well as those of xenos. The character can attempt any Linguistics skill in which he is not trained as an untrained skill test as if it were not a Specialist skill.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Rank 3 in Linguistics (Any)","aptitudes":"Intelligence, Knowledge","benefit":"The character can attempt any Linguistics skill as untrained","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"K7pHq4rkP7SLXjBd"}
{"name":"Hardy","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s constitution allows him to rebound quickly from shock or injury. When undergoing medical treatment or healing from injuries, he always recovers damage as if Lightly Damaged, regardless of the level of damage he sustained.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Toughness 40","aptitudes":"Toughness, Defence","benefit":"Character always heals as if Lightly Damaged.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"KaDakMRE3SWJbVqE"}
{"name":"Rites of Banishment","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>In battle against the daemonic, the Acolyte ceaselessly intones sacred rites and invocations against the Daemon, calling on the Emperor to cast the abominations back into the Warp. These holy words disrupt the Daemon&rsquo;s hold in the material universe, weakening its malefic form.</p>\n<p>Effect: Once per round as a Half Action, the character may speak the litanies and invocations to disrupt Daemons. Until the beginning of his next turn, Daemons within a distance equal to twice the character&rsquo;s Willpower bonus in meters suffer a &ndash;10 penalty to Willpower tests.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Common Lore (Imperial Creed) +10 or Forbidden Lore (Daemonology)","aptitudes":"Offence, Willpower","benefit":"speak the litanies and Daemons suffer a –10 penalty to WP tests","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"LxpkEgrF4Qwa0RYs"}
{"name":"Deny the Witch","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte draws on his faith and mental fortitude to act as his shield against those tainted by the Warp. The character may use his Willpower characteristic when making an Evasion Reaction against ranged or melee attacks against him made with psychic powers. When successfully evading an attack with an area of effect, the character does not move but instead is simply unaffected by the psychic power.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Willpower 35","aptitudes":"Willpower, Defence","benefit":"Can use Willpower to Evade against psychic attacks.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"MF9X9aaLN0eu9RAG"}
{"name":"Archivator","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Whether through years of experience or specialised training, the Acolyte is a master of mining information from the Imperium&rsquo;s countless archives. From delving into deep info-crypts to searching mouldering librarium stacks and deciphering ancient tech-slabs, the Acolyte can uncover knowledge thought long lost. When making a Scholastic Lore or Forbidden Lore test utilising sources of recorded information of any sort, such as cogitators, tomes, info-nets, and data-slates, the character can reroll a failed test once with a &ndash;10 penalty. In addition, tests to perform research or find information in these circumstances take half the usual time.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Int 40","aptitudes":"Knowledge, Perception","benefit":"The Acolyte is a master of mining information from the Imperium’s countless archives.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"QzxIYF6IOsYsqa0C"}
{"name":"Face in a Crowd","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>A successful investigation often involves trailing suspects without their knowledge, the better to follow them to hidden dens of heretical worship or criminal activity. With training, the Acolyte can ensure none notice his presence, through careful replication of a crowd&rsquo;s mannerisms or even joining gatherings while still keeping a careful eye on his quarry. When employing the Shadowing special use of the Stealth skill, he can use his Fellowship characteristic instead of his Agility.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Clues from the Crowds, Fellowship 35","aptitudes":"Fellowship, Social","benefit":"Can use Fellowship instead of Agility when Shadowing","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"SKy5MhKxV5aWHg0l"}
{"name":"Coordinated Interrogation","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>A trained Acolyte, especially when working in conjunction with fellow veteran Acolytes, can induce cooperation from even the most hardened of suspects and captured heretics. He gains a +10 bonus to all Interrogation tests, and gains an additional +5 for each other character participating in the interrogation who also has Coordinated Interrogation. This counts as test assistance, and thus also gains the standard assistance bonuses as per page 25.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Clues from the Crowds, Strength 40 or Willpower 40","aptitudes":"Intelligence, Social","benefit":"+10 bonus to all Interrogate tests, additional +5 for others who also have Coordinated Interrogation.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"TT5Bp55nkuOkWBWE"}
{"name":"Unarmed Specialist","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>After extensive training, the Acolyte has made his body as dangerous as any Munitorum-issued weapon. He gains the Deadly Natural Weapon trait (see page 135), and counts as armed even when facing weapon-wielding opponents while barehanded. While fighting barehanded, he can also re-roll the damage he inflicts.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Agility 35, Ambidextrous, Weapon Skill 35","aptitudes":"Strength, Offence","benefit":"When fighting unarmed, attacks hit as Deadly Natural Weapons and user can re-roll damage.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"VMArGbBP9tEKymfT"}
{"name":"Battle Rage","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Long experience and indomitable will have allowed the character to master the beast within, directing its rage while keeping his head, despite the howling bloodlust in his mind. The Acolyte can Parry while Frenzied, and can re-roll a failed test to snap out of Frenzy or resist entering Frenzy if he so chooses.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Frenzy","aptitudes":"Strength, Defence","benefit":"Parry while frenzied.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"W2koKYDBflMk2I2S"}
{"name":"Precision Killer*","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p><strong>Specialisations:</strong> Ranged, Melee</p>\n<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s eye, hand, and weapon act seamlessly together, placing his attacks exactly where he intends. When this talent is taken, the character selects the Specialisation that matches the Characteristic and Aptitude pair (Ballistic Skill or Weapon Skill) used in purchase. When making a Called Shot (see page 219) with a melee or ranged attack (depending on the Specialisation), he does not suffer the usual &ndash;20 penalty.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Ballistic Skill 40 or Weapon Skill 40","aptitudes":"Ballistic Skill or Weapon Skill, Finesse","benefit":"No penalty to making Called Shot in either Ranged  or Melee Combat.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"WFkom3AcUeQfXbG3"}
{"name":"Cover-Up","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Even the slightest whisper of the Inquisition&rsquo;s presence can be enough to scatter suspected heretics and drive cults into hiding. To prevent the growth and spread of rumours, Acolytes use combinations of well-placed bribes, dire threats, and other means to keep their activities as secretive as possible. At the GM&rsquo;s discretion, the character can reduce his Influence to increase his group&rsquo;s Subtlety. For every point of Influence lost in this way, the Acolyte increases his warband&rsquo;s Subtlety by 1d5.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Intelligence 35","aptitudes":"Intelligence, Knowledge","benefit":"Can reduce Influence by 1 to gain 1d5 Subtlety.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"a1QGHlkPypi8N1kz"}
{"name":"Counter Attack","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s lightning ripostes are things of deadly beauty; swift and invisible as the wind. Once per turn, after successfully Parrying an opponent&rsquo;s attack, this character may immediately make a Standard Attack action as a Free Action against that opponent using the weapon with which he Parried. The character suffers a &ndash;20 penalty on the Weapon Skill test for this attack.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Weapon Skill 40","aptitudes":"Weapon Skill, Defence","benefit":"May attack after successful Parry","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"aCGaQvaONnjDSqcy"}
{"name":"Maglev Transcendence","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte has learned how to better use his implanted maglev coils, and can hover for a number of minutes equal to 1d10 plus twice his Toughness bonus. He can move his Run speed when making a Half Move action and suffers no damage from falling if the coils are active. Each use drains half the power stored in the coils (therefore he can use the coils twice before recharging them).</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Maglev Coils, Mechanicus Implants","aptitudes":"Intelligence, Tech","benefit":"Character can hover for longer periods of time.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"cJlfqrGlbgY8SSPJ"}
{"name":"Exotic Weapon Training*","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p><strong>Specialisations:</strong> Each different exotic weapon</p>\n<p>The Acolyte is trained to use a particularly obscure type of weapon, such as a graviton gun or needle pistol. Weapons requiring this unique talent are noted in their armoury descriptions. Unlike other kinds of weapons training, this talent applies only to a single weapon type and not a class of weapons. Note that an Exotic weapon with the Heavy class would also require the Weapon Training (Heavy) talent as well as Exotic Weapon Training in that specific weapon.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"None","aptitudes":"Intelligence, Finesse","benefit":"Gain proficiency with one exotic weapon type.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"dCmS0x2HmNFpvEjN"}
{"name":"Luminen Shock","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The energies charged in the Acolyte&rsquo;s Luminen Capacitors can be expelled by touching a foe. The character always counts as being equipped with a melee weapon that inflicts 1d10 plus his WPB in Energy damage, with Pen 0 and the Shocking quality. He always counts as having Weapon Training for it and after making this attack, he must pass a Toughness test or suffer 1 level of Fatigue.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Luminen Capacitors, Mechanicus Implants","aptitudes":"Weapon Skill, Tech","benefit":"Character can discharge energy in melee attack.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ddCQQdR96QbRVSOF"}
{"name":"One-on-One","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte is a master of single combat. Without the distractions of multiple opponents, he fights at his best, taking every opening and leaving none.</p>\n<p>Effect: When fighting a single enemy in melee combat, the character scores extra degrees of success on successful Weapon Skill tests equal to half of his Weapon Skill bonus (rounded down).</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Weapon Skill 40","aptitudes":"Finesse, Weapon Skill","benefit":"extra DOS in One on One Meele","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"dnPpFfiazYGelqVn"}
{"name":"Field Vivisection*","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Specialisations: Ranged, Melee</p>\n<p>The Acolyte is well-versed in the blasphemous anatomy of his xenos foes, and uses this knowledge to utmost effect, both in the laboratorium and on the battlefield. Each time this talent is taken, the character selects the Specialisation that matches the Characteristic and Aptitude pair (Ballistic Skill or Weapon Skill) used in purchase. When using the Called Shot action with a melee or ranged attack (depending on the Specialisation) against a target for which the character has the appropriate Forbidden Lore (Xenos) skill, he makes a Medicae (WS) or Medicae (BS) test in place of the normal Weapon Skill or Ballistic Skill test.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Ballistic Skill or Weapon Skill 40, Forbidden Lore (Xenos–Any), Rank 2 in the Medicae skill","aptitudes":"Ballistic Skill or Weapon Skill, Knowledge","benefit":"Know the anatomy of your xenos foes","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"e1XFhbcBDf1XKJ6t"}
{"name":"Hard Target","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Light on his feet, the Acolyte dodges and weaves as he moves, skills learned from long years in the line of fire. When he performs a Charge or Run action, opponents suffer a &ndash;20 penalty to Ballistic Skill tests made to hit him with ranged attacks. This penalty continues until the start of his next turn.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Agility 40","aptitudes":"Agility, Defence","benefit":"–20 to hit character when he Charges or Runs.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"eUpjEQT8gHc8i6by"}
{"name":"Strong Minded","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s mind acts as a fortress against psychic attacks. He can re-roll failed Willpower tests to resist any psychic powers that affect his mind. This talent does not affect psychic powers that have a physical effect, such as Smite or Assail.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Resistance (Psychic Powers), Willpower 30","aptitudes":"Willpower, Defence","benefit":"May reroll failed WP tests to resist psychic powers.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"g4EyZNCql3Vxi1LM"}
{"name":"Constant Vigilance*","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p><strong>Specialisations:</strong> Intelligence, Perception</p>\n<p>From years of surviving ambushes and surprise attacks, the Acolyte is always ready for battle. His subconscious is alert to the slightest footstep or activation of a lasgun pack, and he acts often before he is fully aware of the threat. When this talent is taken, the character selects the Specialisation that matches the prerequisite (Perception or Intelligence) used in purchase. He can use the characteristic that matches that Specialisation when rolling for Initiative instead of his Agility value, and rolls two dice for the roll (picking the highest of the two for his score).</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Awareness +10, Intelligence 35 or Perception 35","aptitudes":"Perception, Defence","benefit":"Can use Per or Int instead of Ag for Initiative rolls, and rolls two dice (picking higher) for the result.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"gfKNxQKsxUbehKNr"}
{"name":"Two-Weapon Wielder","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Intensive training allows the Acolyte to use a weapon in each hand when needed. When armed with two one-handed weapons (ether melee or ranged weapons), after making a Half Action attack (this can be a Single Attack, a Swift Attack, or a Lightning Attack with a melee weapon, or it can be a single shot, semi-auto burst, or full auto burst with a ranged weapon), he can make a single additional Half Action attack following the same restrictions with the other weapon as a Free Action. In effect, this allows him to attack twice in a round, once from each of his weapons. Both of these attacks count as being part of the same Half Action, and both tests made to attack with the weapons suffer a &ndash;20 penalty.</p>\n<p>This talent can be taken twice, each time with a different specialisation (melee or ranged). If he possesses both talents, then he can fight with one melee and one ranged weapon. When this talent is taken with the melee focus it counts as having the Weapon Skill and Finesse aptitudes, and when it is taken with the ranged focus it counts as having the Ballistic Skill and Finesse aptitudes.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"None","aptitudes":"Melee, Ranged","benefit":"May fight with two weapons.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"gowwCmjcsKuoBbqP"}
{"name":"Daemonhunter","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Through years of experience and countless encounters that would blast the sanity and soul of a lesser man, the Acolyte has honed his abilities to uncover and destroy the Daemon wherever it may be found. He knows and recognises the spoor of the Daemon, and his righteous anger ensures that his blows land squarely on the unholy adversary.</p>\n<p>Effect: The Acolyte may re-roll failed Awareness and Psyniscience tests to detect the presence of Daemons. In addition, his attacks against Daemons gain the Proven (3) quality.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Forbidden Lore (Daemonology), Willpower 40","aptitudes":"Intelligence, Tech","benefit":"re-roll failed Awareness and Psyniscience tests","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"iOrObPoUBod58QiM"}
{"name":"Double Tap","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte is practiced in making dual attacks, and can almost subconsciously tell when his hits strike to best effect. When making a second ranged attack action in the same turn against the same target, he gains a +20 bonus to the attack test if his first attack scored one or more successful hits.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Two-Weapon Wielder","aptitudes":"Finesse, Offence","benefit":"Successful first attack grants bonus to second attack.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"l84DGocsjuKWN2XA"}
{"name":"Bulging Biceps","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Whereas a weaker man might be sent flying by the recoil of a heavy weapon, this Acolyte&rsquo;s strong physique allows him to remain standing. He can fire a heavy weapon using Semi-Auto Burst or Full Auto Burst without bracing the weapon, and does not suffer the &ndash;30 penalty for failing to brace it. In addition, whenever he uses the Heft special use of the Athletics skill (see page 98) he can add +20 to his Athletics skill test to reflect his powerful musculature.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Strength 45","aptitudes":"Strength, Offence","benefit":"Remove bracing requirement from Heavy weapons.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"lKxzcLADZgR3PxX8"}
{"name":"Contact Network","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Acolytes rely on a web of relationships, favours, debts, and obligations that can range from within a hab-block to spanning an entire system. Developing and exploiting this network properly allows them to gain access to weapons, travel berths, personnel, and other resources when needed; those who maximise their connections can ensure they are well-armed and well-prepared as they face a new heresy. An Acolyte with this talent can use his Fellowship characteristic in place of his Influence when making Requisition tests (see page 142).</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Cover-Up, Intelligence 35","aptitudes":"Fellowship, Leadership","benefit":"Use Fellowship instead of Influence for Requisition tests.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"lRx7O92H0uGszpHL"}
{"name":"Inescapable Attack*","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte can anticipate his opponent&rsquo;s reactions, and ensures his hits strike no matter how a foe tries to avoid them. This talent applies to Melee or Ranged attacks, depending on the Speciality chosen. After making a successful attack test of the appropriate type as part of an All Out Attack, Called Shot, Charge, Standard Attack, or Stun action, the character imposes a penalty on all evasion attempts (Dodge or Parry tests) made against this attack equal to 10 times the total degrees of success scored on the attack test.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Ballistic Skill 40 or Weapon Skill 40, Perception 35","aptitudes":"Ballistic Skill or Weapon Skill, Finesse","benefit":"Attacker imposes penalty on DoS from Evasion test equal to DoS his initial attack.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"moKpKwYGJGL2dZqD"}
{"name":"Hotshot Pilot","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>When the situation calls for it, the opeator stretches the bounds of his abilities, displaying impressive feats of manoeuvring. This experience has also taught the Acolyte how to recover from what might become fatal mishaps for a less skilled operator attempting such manoeuvres. When the Acolyte succeeds on an Operate test (or Survival test in the case of a living steed), he may voluntarily suffer 1 level of Fatigue to add a number of degrees of success equal to half of his Agility bonus. When the Acolyte fails an Operate test (or Survival test in the case of a living steed), he may voluntarily suffer 1 level of Fatigue in order to reduce the degrees of failure by an amount equal to his Agility bonus, to a minimum of 1.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Rank 2 in Survival or any Operate skill, Agility 35","aptitudes":"Agility, Tech","benefit":"Fatigue for DOS in operate/survival rolls","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"n2o3bexR1MjaGhyE"}
{"name":"Penitent Psyker","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Psykers are hated and shunned throughout the Imperium, and even those psykers who serve the Emperor often struggle with their curse. Whether a rogue psyker taken under an Inquisitor&rsquo;s wing or a sanctioned psyker whose faith condemns his abilities, such an individual might develop the ability to act as a kind of psychic lightning rod, sacrificing his own lesh in order to protect his allies from the Warp-spawned powers of the witch and wyrd.&nbsp; When the psyker or an ally within 10 metres becomes the target of a psychic power, the psyker may voluntarily sufer any number of levels of Fatigue. Each level of Fatigue sufered grants the target a +10 bonus on any Opposed test to resist the power or Evasion test to avoid its efects. If the target&rsquo;s test to resist or avoid the power results in a roll of doubles, the psyker generates Psychic Phenomena, just as if he had used the Focus Power action.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Psy rating, Strong Minded, Willpower 40","aptitudes":"Psyker, Defence","benefit":"Protect an ally from psychic attacks","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"oQWjNcyZD8QBzXeu"}
{"name":"Swift Attack","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s ability with weapons is legendary, allowing him to attack with amazing speed in melee. He can make the Swift Attack action (see page 225).</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Weapon Skill 30","aptitudes":"Weapon Skill, Finesse","benefit":"May make multiple melee attacks.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"rt3VhVL8zaAocN1c"}
{"name":"Witch Finder","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>In order to root out the witch, wyrd, and sorcerer, an Inquisitor or Acolyte must be able to detect and follow the sign and spoor of the psyker. Although some are themselves psykers, or employ the services of such, others train their own senses and mind to detect even the subtlest traces of psychic activity. The character counts as possessing the Psyniscience skill at Rank 1 (Known), even though he is not a psyker. Note that he cannot spend experience to gain additional ranks in the skill.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Rank 2 (Trained) in the Forbidden Lore (Psykers) skill, Willpower 45","aptitudes":"Knowledge, Perception","benefit":"gain  Psyniscience skill at Rank 1","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"sC3jSlEM0VrYLJWl"}
{"name":"Iron Resolve","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte is inured to the terrors of both combat and the</p>\n<p>Warp, knowing that he must control his fear in order to face foes that threaten both body and soul. When confronted with the machinations of heretics, threats to life and limb, and even the otherworldly creatures of the Warp, the Acolyte stands firm.</p>\n<p>Effect: After failing a Fear or Pinning test, the character can re-roll the test with a &ndash;10 modifier.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Intelligence 35, Tech-Use, Trade (Armourer)","aptitudes":"Defence, Willpower","benefit":"re-roll failed fear/pinning test","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"spVoghSrDHoKttho"}
{"name":"Combat Master","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s weapon seems to be everywhere at once, keeping many more opponents at bay in close combat than would seem possible. Opponents fighting him in hand-to-hand combat gain no bonuses for Ganging Up (see page 229).</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Weapon Skill 30","aptitudes":"Weapon Skill, Defence","benefit":"Opponents get no bonus for outnumbering the character.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"tIc600LmSxKBVs7v"}
{"name":"Hip Shooting","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s prowess with ranged weapons is such that he can still fire accurately without his eye behind the sights. As a Full Action, he can both move up to his Full Move rate and make a single attack with a ranged weapon. This attack can only be a single shot, and so cannot be a semi- or full-automatic ranged attack for example. Characters with the Two-Weapon Fighting talent can use this talent with Hip Shooting to make two single shots, if they are armed with a ranged weapon in each hand.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Agility 40, Ballistic Skill 40","aptitudes":"Ballistic Skill, Finesse","benefit":"Characters may shoot when moving.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"toZfWSO6yYoX0ekh"}
{"name":"Armour-Monger","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte is a skilled armourer, and constantly tinkers and improves his armour, or keeps it in pristine shape by repairing the slightest damage it sustains. With years of training, he has even learned to enhance the protection afforded by his armour and how to use it to its optimum. The character gains an extra amount of Armour points equal to his Intelligence bonus, which he can distribute to any locations that his armour would normally cover, as long as he has at least an hour each day to clean and repair it or make minor modifications. This bonus applies only to armour when the Acolyte is wearing it, as it combines his training with his skill at armoury.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Intelligence 35, Tech-Use, Trade (Armourer)","aptitudes":"Intelligence, Tech","benefit":"Increase the efficacy of physical armour.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ufTbwX4Clzq5Gc8I"}
{"name":"Killing Strike","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>With expert precision, the Acolyte can land blows which defy his opponent&rsquo;s ability to counter, slicing through defences as surely as a powerblade cuts flesh. At the beginning of each of his turns, the character may spend a Fate point to make his melee attacks unavoidable with the Dodge and Parry skills until the end of the round. Other means of avoiding or stopping attacks (such as displacer fields or alien protective devices) are unaffected.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Weapon Skill 50","aptitudes":"Weapon Skill, Offence","benefit":"Spend Fate point to make melee attacks unavoidable","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"uhyATVxWyBOkxuLc"}
{"name":"Whirlwind of Deat","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>When facing massed opponents in close quarters, the Acolyte becomes a streak of blows, moving, hacking, gutting, and beheading his enemies with ceaseless fury. As a Half Action, the character may make one Standard Attack action (see page 224) with a melee weapon against a foe, plus one additional Standard Attack action with the same weapon targeting each other foe also engaged in melee combat with the character beyond the first (to a maximum number of attacks up to his Weapon Skill bonus).</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Weapon Skill 40","aptitudes":"Weapon Skill, Finesse","benefit":"Make one attack for each melee opponent.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"wE8Yi9s8a2H6fIok"}
{"name":"Ambassador Imperialis","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>Whether from serving in the fleet of a Rogue Trader or dealing with xenos mercenaries on frontier worlds, the Acolyte is experienced in dealing with alien and the most divergent of non-Imperial cultures, able to avoid the subtle faux pas that can so easily cause a negotiation to deteriorate into bloodshed. The character reduces any penalty to Interaction skill tests for dealing with xenos or non-Imperial NPCs by 20. In addition, once per encounter, he can reroll a failed Interaction skill test when interacting with such an NPC.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Fellowship 35, Intelligence 35","aptitudes":"Perception, Social","benefit":"reduces any penalty to Interaction skill tests for dealing with xenos or non-Imperial NPCs by 20.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"wVr6bTdzNNtsRR7r"}
{"name":"Marksman","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":"<p>The Acolyte&rsquo;s steady hand and eagle eye allow him to keep crosshairs steady on any target, regardless of range. Distance is no protection against the character&rsquo;s marksmanship, and he suffers no penalties for making Ballistic Skill tests at Long or Extreme range.</p>","source":"","prerequisites":"Ballistic Skill 35","aptitudes":"Ballistic Skill, Finesse","benefit":"No penalties for firing at long or extreme range.","tier":2,"cost":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/dh2e_Resources/icons/Talents/2.svg","effects":[],"_id":"zgLFOQQSnjDLa9sJ"}
